Westchester municipalities

Most recent data: Dec 23, 2020

The municipality with the most new cases per capita in the past 14 days is Mount Kisco, where there have been an average of 11 new cases per day reported between Dec 9, 2020 and Dec 23, 2020 (99 per 100,000 residents). Elmsford is another recent hot spot, with 4 new cases per day reported in the last two weeks (93 per 100,000).

Throughout the pandemic, the municipalities that have had the largest share of their population test positive for coronavirus are Elmsford (1 in 11) and Port Chester (1 in 11). The municipalities that have had the fewest cases per capita are Pound Ridge (1 in 49) and Irvington (1 in 33).
